A card is a self-contained UI component that displays information about a single subject, such as a game or a category. Large card for League of Legends and smaller cards for Fortnite, Call of Duty, and another Call of Duty.
A button is a clickable element that triggers an action. There are follow buttons and a large purple button on the League of Legends card.
A badge is a small UI component that displays a label or a category. Badges are used to categorize games, such as MOBA, ESport, and Shooter.
An icon is a small visual element that represents an action or a category. There are icons for navigation and game categories.
An icon button is a button that uses an icon to represent an action. There are icon buttons for navigation.
A divider is a visual element that separates content. There is a divider between the cards.
Typography is used to display text in different styles and sizes. Headings and body text are used throughout the component.
An image is a visual element that displays a picture. Images are used to represent games and categories.
A carousel is a UI component that displays a series of content. There is a carousel with navigation icons.
A grid is a layout component that displays content in a grid. The cards are arranged in a grid layout.
